 According to information, two robbers sprayed employees at Pep Home with pepper spray and made off with cash. Middelburg Mall security guards confronted the robbers on their way out but had to back off when one of them produced and pointed at them with a fire-arm. The robbers fled in a golden Mercedes with the Middelburg Mall’s armed security guard giving chase. Also read: Four suspects on the loose after armed robbery Middelburg Mall manager Mike Tammadge said that no one was injured in the robbery. Although guards inside the mall are not armed, to ensure the safety of shoppers, armed guards are present outside the mall to assist in instances such as the current situation. Mr Tammadge said that the last update he got was the guards were still in pursuit of the suspects and that the help of the police were called in.      One dead in early morning crash Fake notes in Belfast leads to two arrests Theft of motor vehicles on the rise Accident claims the life of an infant • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za